# ============================================================================
# API Testing for Overdue Functionality
# Use with REST Client extension in VS Code or Postman
# ============================================================================

### 1. Test manual overdue job trigger (if TestController is added)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/test/trigger-overdue-job
Content-Type: application/json

### 2. Login as Owner
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "owner@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Get Collection Dashboard Data (replace YOUR_TOKEN with actual token)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/owner/reports/collection-summary
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN

### 4. Get specific tenant installments
GET http://localhost:8080/api/owner/reports/tenant/TENANT_ID/installments
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN

### 5. Login as Tenant to see overdue from tenant perspective
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "tenant@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 6. Get Tenant Dashboard (should show overdue count)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tenant/dashboard
Authorization: Bearer TENANT_TOKEN